GIT:
Git is a version control system.
Git helps to keep track of code changes.
Git is used to collaborate on code.

GITHUB:
GitHub is a web-based Git repository hosting service.

GitHub Alternatives:
Bitbucket
GitBucket

Example:
A person wants to drink fruit juice.
Fruits and a mixie are required.
Fruits – Git
Mixie – GitHub

Git is the backbone.
Some Git operations can be performed through GitHub.
Both are popular tools and are mostly used in IT areas.
